From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: remove deprecated label from sdhc-spi-slot node

NCS 2.7 / Zephyr 3.6 deprecates the `label` DT property. The omi
overlay still has `label = "SDHC_0"` on sdhc@0, which can silently
break binding matching. Build evidence: only subsys/disk/disk_access.c
compiles; sdhc_spi.c / sdmmc_subsys.c / sd.c don't build at all,
which is why disk_access_init('SD') returns -EINVAL (no disk
registered).

Drop the label. Let the binding match by `compatible` alone.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay b/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
@@ -8,7 +8,6 @@
         compatible = "zephyr,sdhc-spi-slot";
         reg = <0>;
         status = "okay";
-        label = "SDHC_0";
         mmc {
             compatible = "zephyr,sdmmc-disk";
             status = "okay";
